ation#environment-variables","content":"Workspace directory the runner executes workflows in"},"979":{"id":"/guides/installation-79","page_id":"/guides/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/installation#environment-variables","content":"`SMITHERS_RUNNER_LOCATION`"},"980":{"id":"/guides/installation-80","page_id":"/guides/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/installation#environment-variables","content":"Location label (`vps` or `local`) used for run routing"},"981":{"id":"/guides/installation-81","page_id":"/guides/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/installation#environment-variables","content":"`SMITHERS_RUNNER_NAME` / `SMITHERS_RUNNER_TAGS`"},"982":{"id":"/guides/installation-82","page_id":"/guides/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/installation#environment-variables","content":"Runner display name and capability tags"},"983":{"id":"/guides/installation-83","page_id":"/guides/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/installation#environment-variables","content":"`SMITHERS_RUNNER_CONCURRENCY`"},"984":{"id":"/guides/installation-84","page_id":"/guides/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/installation#environment-variables","content":"Max concurrent runs (default 1)"},"985":{"id":"/guides/installation-85","page_id":"/guides/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/installation#where-state-lives","content":"Everything durable is in the Hub's data directory (`RUNYARD_HUB_DATA_DIR`,\ndefault `data/`; the `hub-data` volume mounted at `/data` in containers). It\nsurvives every update and rollback:"},"986":{"id":"/guides/installation-86","page_id":"/guides/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/installation#where-state-lives","content":"`runyard.sqlite` — the SQLite database (runs, workflows, tokens, schedules,\napprovals, encrypted secrets)"},"987":{"id":"/guides/installation-87","page_id":"/guides/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/installation#where-state-lives","content":"`artifacts/` — uploaded run artifacts"},"988":{"id":"/guides/installation-88","page_id":"/guides/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/installation#where-state-lives","content":"`bootstrap-token.txt` — the first admin token, generated on first boot\n(mode `0600`); use it to sign in once and mint scoped tokens"},"989":{"id":"/guides/installation-89","page_id":"/guides/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/installation#where-state-lives","content":"`session-secret.txt` — the persisted dev session secret when none is provided"},"990":{"id":"/guides/installation-90","page_id":"/guides/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/installation#where-state-lives","content":"Back this directory up. The runner workspace, by contrast, is disposable\nscratch space — outputs and event traces are uploaded to the Hub as artifacts."},"991":{"id":"/guides/installation-91","page_id":"/guides/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/installation#next-steps","content":"Point clients at the Hub: CLI guide, MCP guide"},"992":{"id":"/guides/installation-92","page_id":"/guides/installation","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/installation#next-steps","content":"Drive it over HTTP: API guide"},"993":{"id":"/guides/mcp","page_id":"/guides/mcp","type":"page","content":"MCP","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Guides"],"tags":[],"url":"/guides/mcp"},"994":{"id":"/guides/mcp-0","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp","content":"Connect AI agents to a Runyard Hub with the runyard-mcp stdio server and its 85-tool surface."},"995":{"id":"/guides/mcp-1","page_id":"/guides/mcp","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/mcp#install-and-configure","content":"Install and configure"},"996":{"id":"/guides/mcp-2","page_id":"/guides/mcp","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/mcp#hub-url-and-token-resolution","content":"Hub URL and token resolution"},"997":{"id":"/guides/mcp-3","page_id":"/guides/mcp","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/mcp#the-tool-surface","content":"The tool surface"},"998":{"id":"/guides/mcp-4","page_id":"/guides/mcp","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/mcp#the-parity-guarantee","content":"The parity guarantee"},"999":{"id":"/guides/mcp-5","page_id":"/guides/mcp","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/mcp#recommended-agent-flow","content":"Recommended agent flow"},"1000":{"id":"/guides/mcp-6","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp","content":"`runyard-mcp` is a stdio Model Context Protocol\nserver that ships with the Runyard CLI. It runs locally next to your AI client\n(Claude Code, Claude Desktop, Codex, Cursor, and others), and translates every\ntool call into an authenticated HTTP request against your Hub. No workflow\nlogic runs in the MCP server itself — it is a thin, faithful client of the\nHTTP API."},"1001":{"id":"/guides/mcp-7","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#install-and-configure","content":"Install the CLI first (it bundles `runyard-mcp`) and log in — see the\nCLI guide:"},"1002":{"id":"/guides/mcp-8","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#install-and-configure","content":"Then let the CLI write your AI client's MCP config:"},"1003":{"id":"/guides/mcp-9","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#install-and-configure","content":"Supported `--client` values: `claude-code`, `claude-desktop`, `codex`,\n`cursor`, `windsurf`, `gemini`, `vscode`. Each writes the appropriate config\nfile (for example `.mcp.json` for Claude Code, `~/.codex/config.toml` for\nCodex, `.vscode/mcp.json` for VS Code) and prints how to activate it."},"1004":{"id":"/guides/mcp-10","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#install-and-configure","content":"To configure a client by hand, print the snippet instead:"},"1005":{"id":"/guides/mcp-11","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#hub-url-and-token-resolution","content":"The server name is `runyard` for the default remote and `runyard-<remote>` for\nothers, so one client can talk to several Hubs. &#x2A;*No token is stored in client\nconfigs.** At startup the server resolves its target in this order:"},"1006":{"id":"/guides/mcp-12","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#hub-url-and-token-resolution","content":"`RUNYARD_HUB_URL` / `RUNYARD_HUB_TOKEN` environment variables\n(legacy `SMITHERS_HUB_URL` / `SMITHERS_HUB_TOKEN` and `HUB_URL` / `HUB_TOKEN`\nstill work)"},"1007":{"id":"/guides/mcp-13","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#hub-url-and-token-resolution","content":"The `--remote <name>` argument, resolved against the saved remotes in\n`~/.runyard/config.json` (written by `runyard login`)"},"1008":{"id":"/guides/mcp-14","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#hub-url-and-token-resolution","content":"The current saved remote"},"1009":{"id":"/guides/mcp-15","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#hub-url-and-token-resolution","content":"The token's scopes decide what the tools may do — a token with `mcp` scope can\ndiscover, preflight, and run workflows; `admin` unlocks the admin tools listed\nbelow."},"1010":{"id":"/guides/mcp-16","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#the-tool-surface","content":"The server exposes **85 tools**, generated from the same API surface registry\nthe Hub's routes and `/openapi.json` come from. Grouped by resource:"},"1011":{"id":"/guides/mcp-17","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#the-tool-surface","content":"Group"},"1012":{"id":"/guides/mcp-18","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#the-tool-surface","content":"Tools"},"1013":{"id":"/guides/mcp-19","page_id":"/guides/mcp","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/mcp#the-tool-surface","content":"Discovery & iden