9":1079,"1180":761,"1181":259,"1182":837,"1183":717,"1184":296,"1185":1154,"1186":918,"1187":159,"1188":1185,"1189":1043,"1190":394,"1191":294,"1192":297,"1193":449,"1194":448,"1195":375,"1196":100,"1197":505,"1198":754,"1199":1197,"1200":994,"1201":1059,"1202":1215,"1203":192,"1204":1052,"1205":396,"1206":1187,"1207":393,"1208":1228,"1209":233,"1210":749,"1211":586,"1212":636,"1213":648,"1214":486,"1215":1189,"1216":833,"1217":1153,"1218":1248,"1219":659,"1220":595,"1221":713,"1222":825,"1223":418,"1224":1040,"1225":295,"1226":751,"1227":151,"1228":1217,"1229":131,"1230":609,"1231":261,"1232":777,"1233":299,"1234":778,"1235":378,"1236":1062,"1237":114,"1238":1226,"1239":452,"1240":705,"1241":454,"1242":1156,"1243":453,"1244":1038,"1245":1144,"1246":638,"1247":870,"1248":1035,"1249":762,"1250":1092,"1251":537,"1252":757,"1253":1152},"orderedDocs":[[293,"—"],[296,"—"],[299,"—"],[302,"—"],[507,"—"],[510,"—"],[513,"—"],[382,"(`trigger` is `ticker` for cadence fires, `manual` for run-now.) The run also gets a `run.scheduled` event recording the schedule, cron, and timezone. If the workflow's approval policy requires it, the run starts in `waiting_approval` like any other run."],[126,"**`custom`** — approving a held run releases it to the queue; reject/changes-requested cancel it. On a card without a held run, the decision is simply recorded."],[124,"**`escalation`** — the run already ended: any decision records the call but does not restart the run (re-run it from the run page)."],[663,"**`GET /api/menu`** (authenticated) — the agent-facing menu: workflow catalog,\nlocal/remote execution modes, and follow-up paths. The same data backs the\nMCP `get_menu` tool and `/llms.txt`."],[664,"**`GET /api/version`** (unauthenticated) — product name, version, instance\nname."],[662,"**`GET /openapi.json`** (unauthenticated) — generated from the server's API\nsurface registry, the single source of truth every route is registered from,\nso **every endpoint is documented there**. This guide covers the important\nones; use `/openapi.json` for the full list."],[1052,"**`get_menu`** — orient: catalog, execution modes, follow-up paths."],[1055,"**`get_run_timeline`** — poll with the returned `nextSince` cursor to page\nforward; drop to `get_run_logs` / `get_run_diagnostics` when something looks\nwrong, and fetch results with `get_run_artifacts` + `download_artifact`."],[1053,"**`preflight_workflow`** — dry-run your input; resolve `needs_input`\nquestions and `blocked` blockers before creating anything (or use\n`run_workflow` with `negotiate: true`, or the run-draft tools for a\nmulti-turn negotiation)."],[1054,"**`run_workflow`** — include a short human-readable `input.title` so run\nlists and approval cards read well; choose `executionMode` `local` or\n`remote`."],[1142,"**`SECRETS_ENC_KEY`** — set it once and guard it; rotating the key makes previously stored secrets unreadable."],[125,"**`side_effect`** — approve allows the gated side effect; reject or changes-requested skip it. The run's completed work is unchanged either way."],[123,"**`workflow_gate`** — approving a card holding a `waiting_approval` run releases it; approving a mid-run gate applies the decision to the paused workflow on the runner, which resumes past the gate. Reject/changes-requested cancel a held run, or take the workflow's own deny path mid-run."],[481,"**Admin**"],[258,"**Agents, skills & knowledge** — shared, reusable building blocks (agent roles, skills, knowledge resources) that workflows reference."],[49,"**Agents**"],[475,"**Approvals only**"],[262,"**Approvals** — declared human decisions: approval cards with an explicit ask, per-kind consequences, and optional timers with fallbacks."],[1144,"**Audit log review** — every actor-attributable action lands in the audit log (`runyard audit`, `GET /api/audit`, `get_audit_log`)."],[914,"**Clients** — the `runyard` CLI, the `runyard-mcp` MCP server, and the web app\nare all ordinary API clients of the Hub."],[266,"**Deep links** — the shareable URL grammar of the Hub web app, plus the deep links the API returns in its payloads."],[378,"**Disable** stops a schedule from firing without deleting it; **enable** resumes the cadence. Both are admin actions."],[469,"**Everything** (default)"],[263,"**Hooks** — admin-defined post-run side effects (publish, push, webhook) that run after a run's gates pass and never fail a green run."],[912,"**Hub** — the HTTP server: API, web UI, MCP-backing endpoints, and the embedded\nSQLite datastore. One per deployment."],[53,"**Knowledge**"],[627,"**Poll the timeline with `since` cursors.** `get_run_timeline` (`GET /api/runs/{id}/timeline`) returns a unified, ascending view of status transitions, events, and artifacts. Pass the previous response's `nextSince` as `since` so the Hub never re-sends what you have. Fetch results with `get_run_status`, `get_run_logs`, and `get_run_artifacts` / `download_artifact`."],[625,"**Preflight first.** When input is rough or unverified, call `preflight_workflow` (`POST /api/workflows/{id}/preflight`) or pass `negotiate: true` to `run_workflow`. You get `ready | needs_input | blocked` with concrete questions and blockers instead of a run that fails."],[341,"**Promotion** — for runs that mutated an isolated git worktree, `POST /api/runs/{id}/promote` merges the successful run's work into its target branch, runs gates, pushes, and cleans up the branch/worktree. Merging to the default branch always goes through promotion, never through a hook."],[457,"**Read-only.** Inspect workflows, runs, logs, artifacts, approvals, schedules, runners, and the menu — and nothing else. It satisfies no mutation endpoint, so a `read`-only token can never change state."],[472,"**Read-only**"],[652,"**Read-only** — inspect workflows, runs, logs, artifacts, approvals, schedules, and runners; satisfies no mutation endpoint"],[340,"**Rerun** — `POST /api/runs/{id}/rerun` creates a linked new run with the same input, optionally edited."],[337,"**Run drafts** — a draft is a proposed run that has *not* been enqueued. Create it, patch its input to answer questions (each patch re-preflights), then submit; submit re-preflights and returns 202 with the run only when ready (422 `needs_input` / 409 `blocked` otherwise)."],[379,"**Run now** fires the schedule immediately without changing its cadence — useful for testing input before the next scheduled fire."],[478,"**Runner**"],[913,"**Runners** — one or more worker processes that register with the Hub using a\nrunner-scoped token, heartbeat, claim queued runs, and execute workflows. A\nrunner can live on the same host as the Hub or on a separate machine."],[260,"**Runners** — the machines that claim queued runs and execute them via the Smithers engine, with tags, capacity, and optional sandboxing."],[259,"**Runs** — a single execution of a workflow: lifecycle statuses, preflight and run drafts, events, logs, artifacts, reruns, and promotion."],[261,"**Schedules** — cron or one-shot triggers that create ordinary runs on a cadence."],[265,"**Secrets** — an encrypted store whose values are only ever decrypted into a run's child process environment, never returned by the API."],[1141,"**Session secret** — set `RUNYARD_HUB_SESSION_SECRET` explicitly in production (the installer generates one)."],[624,"**Set `input.title`.** For agent-created runs, include a short human-readable title (\"Audit checkout flow mobile states\") so run lists, approval cards, and human handoff stay decipherable."],[51,"**Skills**"],[658,"**Superscope** — satisfies every scope requirement, plus admin-only surfaces: tokens, secrets, audit log, schedules, workflow create/update, packages, hooks, updates"],[834,"**Timer + fallback** — if nobody decides before the deadline, the Hub applies the fallback decision on the human's behalf, fully audited (`resolvedVia: fallback_timer`)."],[835,"**Timer without fallback** — when the timer elapses the card is flagged `fallback_required` and **stays pending**: it is surfaced as urgent, but no decision is ever invented."],[1140,"**TLS reverse proxy** — keep the Hub on `127.0.0.1` and terminate TLS in front (the installer prints a Caddy snippet); set `BASE_URL` to the https URL."],[1143,"**Token hygiene** — issue narrow scopes, set `expiresInDays` on tokens for humans, and revoke with `DELETE /api/tokens/{id}`; retire the bootstrap token once real admin tokens exist."],[264,"**Tokens & scopes** — bearer-token auth with the `api`, `mcp`, `runner`, `approvals`, and `admin` scopes; browser sessions carry exactly a token's scopes."],[1145,"**Updates** — leave `UPDATE_APPLY_ENABLED` off unless you want the admin-gated HTTP apply; prefer `runyard update` on the host. See Releases."],[626,"**Use run drafts for question/answer loops.** `create_run_draft` creates a proposed run and preflights it; `update_run_draft` merges answers into the input and re-preflights; `submit_run_draft` enqueues the real run only once it is ready; `discard_run_draft` abandons it. Nothing executes until submit."],[257,"**Workflows** — the unit of the catalog: a named, versioned definition with input/output schemas whose source lives as immutable bundles in the Hub database."],[883,"`--chain <json>`"],[894,"`--location` is `local` or `vps` and drives run routing (`--where local` runs\nland on `local`-tagged runners). You can also register a machine explicitly:"],[881,"`--negotiate`"],[885,"`--pin <sha>`"],[942,"`--profile proxy` — a bundled Caddy container that terminates TLS for\n`SITE_ADDRESS` and proxies to the Hub. Skip it if you already have a gateway."],[879,"`--runner-location <location>`"],[877,"`--where <mode>`"],[943,"`-f deploy/compose/runner-docker-socket.yml` — give the runner `docker build`\naccess via the host socket (or run a rootless DinD sidecar instead)."],[944,"`-f docker-compose.local.yml` — dev profile using locally built images."],[875,"`-i, --input <json>`"],[80,"`?q=` searches."],[556,"`?q=` searches."],[133,"`?status=pending\\|re