and records both image digests as a release artifact."],[119,"By default a card is blocking: nothing happens until someone decides. Supplying `timeoutMs` or `timeoutAt` at creation makes it a **timed approval**:"],[285,"By default the runner executes workflows directly on its host. Setting `RUNNER_SANDBOX=bubblewrap` on the runner wraps each workflow *launch* in a generated Bubblewrap (`bwrap`) sandbox: the run's workspace is the only writable mount (bound at the same path inside and out), system directories are bound read-only, and the child gets a fresh workspace-local `HOME` — the host home directory, with its keys and credentials, is never mounted. Polling and control commands stay outside the sandbox. Installing `bwrap` is the deployer's responsibility; the runner verifies at startup that the sandbox actually works before claiming runs."],[715,"Cancel; re-queue with same/edited input; merge a successful isolated run into its target branch"],[667,"Canonical"],[271,"Capacity and pool"],[807,"Cards are posted to the configured chat with inline buttons (see below)."],[854,"Cards can deep-link into the Hub as a Telegram WebApp. `POST /api/auth/telegram-webapp` exchanges the WebApp's signed init data for a browser session that is limited to the `approvals` scope — a Telegram identity can review and resolve approval cards, and nothing else. Full app access always requires a real access token."],[47,"Catalog"],[1043,"Catalog"],[1230,"Catalog grouping (for example `Examples`, `Operations`)."],[844,"Chat (group or DM) where approval cards are posted."],[1171,"Check run diagnostics; fix workflow config or runner setup."],[1059,"CI pipeline"],[322,"Claimed by a runner, not yet started."],[939,"claims runs and executes them; workspace volume at `/workspace`"],[1163,"Class"],[514,"Clears the session cookie."],[802,"CLI"],[855,"CLI"],[1091,"CLI"],[784,"CLI guide — the same API from your terminal"],[34,"CLI:"],[1120,"Client install assets."],[846,"Comma-separated Telegram user