et of config keys — anything else is rejected, so raw credentials or ad-hoc shell fragments can never be smuggled into a profile:"],[284,"Each runner declares a `capacity` (concurrent run slots) and reports its active runs; the Hub assigns work only to free slots. `GET /api/runners` returns every registered runner with heartbeat state, capacity, active slots, plus a pool summary — the same data the **Runners** page in the web app shows (`#runners`)."],[380,"Each schedule tracks `nextRunAt`, `lastRunAt`, the last run id, and the last fire status, all visible on the Schedules page (`#schedules`) and in the API."],[180,"Edit the workflow (admin)."],[205,"Effect"],[370,"Enable, disable, run now"],[525,"Enabled and disabled"],[726,"Encrypted secrets store — names and metadata only, never values (admin)"],[59,"Endpoint"],[128,"Endpoint"],[236,"Endpoint"],[286,"Endpoint"],[343,"Endpoint"],[383,"Endpoint"],[427,"Endpoint"],[488,"Endpoint"],[551,"Endpoint"],[773,"Endpoint"],[1107,"Endpoint"],[908,"Environment variables"],[871,"Environment variables `RUNYARD_HUB_URL` / `RUNYARD_HUB_TOKEN` (and an explicit\n`--url` / `--token`) take precedence over the saved remote."],[639,"Error conventions"],[310,"Events, timeline, logs, artifacts"],[122,"Every card answers \"what will my decision do\" honestly, computed from what resolving actually performs:"],[381,"Every fire dispatches a normal run whose origin identifies the schedule:"],[666,"Every grouped operation is also reachable at a stable `/api/v1` alias that\nmakes the group visible in the path — for example:"],[151,"Every Hub URL is shareable - the hash-route grammar of the web app and the deep links the API returns."],[1106,"Every operation requires either a bearer access token (`Authorization: Bearer ...`) or a browser session created by exchanging such a token — and the session carries exactly the token's scopes, no extra power. The unauthenticated surface is deliberately tiny:"],[1069,"Every PR and push to `main` (and tags)"],[447,"Every Runyard API call is authenticated with a **bearer access token**:"],[642,"Every Runyard surface — the web app, the CLI, and the MCP server — is an\nordinary client of one HTTP API served by the Hub. Anything they can do, you\ncan do with `curl`."],[375,"Every schedule has an **IANA timezone** (default `UTC`); the expression is evaluated against wall-clock time in that zone, so DST shifts are honored."],[154,"Every URL in the Runyard web app is shareable: the app is a hash-routed SPA, so any view — a run's logs, a workflow's graph, a pending approval — can be copied from the address bar and opened by anyone with access to the Hub. Links have the form:"],[985,"Everything durable is in the Hub's data directory (`RUNYARD_HUB_DATA_DIR`,\ndefault `data/`; the `hub-data` volume mounted at `/data` in containers). It\nsurvives every update and rollback:"],[463,"Everything. `admin` is a **superscope**: it satisfies every scope requirement, and admin-only endpoints (tokens, secrets, catalog edits, schedules, hooks, audit) require it."],[324,"Executing on the runner."],[253,"Execution"],[1240,"Execution engine; `\"smithers\"`."],[878,"Execution mode: `local` or `remote` (alias: `--execution-mode`)"],[961,"Explicit SQLite database path (default `<data dir>/runyard.sqlite`)"],[308,"Failure classes"],[1151,"Failure classes"],[332,"Failures are classified into specific terminal statuses so operators can tell config problems from real failures: `failed` (generic), `blocked_by_gate` (a verification gate failed), `blocked_by_preflight` (the run could never start as configured), `provider_limited` (rate limits/quota), `timed_out`, `invalid_output` (schema mismatch), `infra_unavailable` (network/runner infrastructure), and `needs_human`."],[113,"Field"],[529,"Field"],[1221,"Field"],[484,"Finer-grained per-group write scopes (e.g. a token that can manage schedules but not run workflows) are a documented follow-up; today `api`/`mcp` grant the whole operating surface."],[326,