obal options `--url`, `--token`,\n`--remote <name>`, and `--json` (machine-readable output)."],[617,"The complete MCP tool set (parity-tested against the API surface). Connect with `runyard mcp install` or the `runyard-mcp` stdio server."],[1250,"The corresponding MCP tools are `get_workflow_source`, `list_workflow_bundles`, and `get_workflow_bundle` (which does include the source). You can also publish a bundle directly with `POST /api/workflow-bundles` / `publish_workflow_bundle` and reference it by `workflow.bundleId`, but prefer inline source — the Hub publishes the bundle for you."],[106,"The creator of a card states the ask up front, and every surface renders it verbatim:"],[1008,"The current saved remote"],[820,"The decision is applied to the paused workflow on the runner and it resumes past the gate."],[413,"The encrypted secret store - admin-managed, listable by name only, delivered to runs at claim time and never returned by the API."],[868,"The fastest path is the install script served by your own Hub, which downloads\nthe CLI tarball from the same instance (`/cli.tgz`), installs `runyard` and\n`runyard-mcp` into `~/.local/bin`, and logs you in:"],[614,"The full HTTP surface, generated from the Hub's API surface registry — it cannot drift from the routes the server actually registers."],[828,"The gated side effect is allowed to run."],[1064,"The GitHub Actions pipeline (`.github/workflows/release.yml` and `images.yml`) has four jobs:"],[816,"The held run is released to the queue and executes."],[234,"The hook did not run."],[837,"The Hub can post approval cards to a Telegram chat and accept decisions from the buttons on them."],[947,"The Hub is a single HTTP listener; any TLS-terminating proxy that forwards **all\npaths** to the Hub port works. With Caddy:"],[928,"The Hub listens on `127.0.0.1:43117` by default. Start a runner in a second\nprocess:"],[918,"The Hub uses the built-in `node:sqlite` module (started with `--experimental-sqlite`)"],[620,"The live, private catalog: workflows with schemas, execution modes, runner pool state, and ready-to-use CLI/MCP invocations."],[268,"The machines that claim and execute runs via the Smithers engine - registration, tags, capacity, health, and sandboxing."],[998,"The parity guarantee"],[940,"The portable base stack is `docker-compose.yml` at the repo root:"],[376,"The preview returns a human-readable description plus the next fire instants — nothing is created."],[230,"The profile cannot execute — typically missing named secrets or a disabled secret store."],[232,"The profile was not eligible for this run."],[1060,"The release-train helper"],[924,"The repository ships a one-command, idempotent bootstrap script for a fresh\nLinux box:"],[930,"The repository ships generic units in `deploy/`. The Hub unit\n(`deploy/runyard.service`):"],[21,"The repository's install script is a one-command, idempotent bootstrap. It installs Node 22 and pnpm if needed, clones Runyard at the latest release tag (default `/opt/runyard`), generates an env file with a `SECRETS_ENC_KEY` and session secret, creates the data directory, and installs systemd units for the Hub and a runner:"],[1136,"The reusable secret store is enabled by setting `SECRETS_ENC_KEY` (a 32-byte key) on the Hub; without a valid key the feature is disabled rather than degraded. Values are encrypted at rest and are write-only from the API's point of view: `GET /api/secrets` returns names and metadata, never values, and secrets are redacted from API responses, events, approval cards, and audit entries. Workflows reference secrets by name; the Hub injects values into runs that declared them."],[1176,"The run exceeded a deadline or an operation timed out."],[421,"the run input's `input.secretNames` list."],[818,"The run is cancelled — a human \"no\" is a decision, not a failure."],[817,"The run is cancelled; your note tells the requester what to change."],[1161,"The run is held on an approval card, which is by design: approval-held